reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Happy with purchase
reviews.reviewText: Holds it shape well. Doesn’t smoosh like some. Smooth zipper and pleasant color and feel.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Turned it into a large first aid kit.
reviews.reviewText: I do not wear much makeup so I didn't get it for that. What I needed was a well organized, durable bag for first aid products. This is exactly what I needed. There is so much room in this bag. I can open it up and immediately find anything I need. There is room for assorted first aid creams in the slots for makeup brushes. Also surgical scissors and several different kinds of tweezers. I left in the detachable divider in the bottom. One side has boxes of different kinds and sizes of bandages, and various wound coverings. The other side holds assorted sizes of elastic bandages, a sling and my tennis elbow brace for when that flares up. The mesh sections hold paper tape and regular tape to hold on bandages. I even have one of those little eye glass cups for washing something out of your eye. Where is that when you need it? I have so many different things in this bag I can't name them all and yet I could fit more.This bag is durable and will last a long time for what I'm using it for. I did cut some red waterproof tape and put crosses on it. The only thing I would change would be to make the handle just a little bit bigger so a man's hand would fit it easier. It's a great bag and worth the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This bag is great for organizing your make up and face products! Honestly I think it is a little too big for me to travel with in a carry on - but it is great to use in your checked bag : ) I used this to organize my make up and face cleaning / treatment products. If you use this bag for more than makeup it definitely helps keep stuff organized and is great to put in your checked bag. It is easy to clean on the outside and inside. I think it's been great to keep all my products organized in my bathroom..... its not just for travel!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love how minimalistic this bag looks from the outside. There is a top compartment that can hold makeup brushes and has a pocket that zips. The bottom compartment holds so much and has a divider that helps you organize your items. This whole bag fits all of my makeup and toiletries when traveling. When at full capacity, it will take up a good amount of your carry on so it may be good for a check in bag since it takes up so much space.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great way to organize makeup and cosmetics on the go
reviews.reviewText: This travel makeup bag is great for people on-the-go or anyone who travels. The portable handle and lightweight design make it suitcase-friendly and easy to carry, and the interior is big enough to hold all my essentials for a weekend trip or daily use. I love its thoughtful organization. The separate brush compartment keeps my brushes clean and organized an the clear lining protects my tools from powder dust. The large clear pocket on the top flap holds my eyeshadow palettes, and two big mesh pockets on the second layer flap provide additional makeup storage. Inside the makeup bag is a spacious interior with a detachable divider, to help organize my other cosmetics. Two small mesh sections and the elastic sections keep everything in place, while the main compartment allows for the storage of oversized items (like a small blow dryer). Overall it’s a great find for keeping my essentials at the ready.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This makeup bag is so big and roomy. I will fit so much of my makeup and cleaners that I will only have to take this one and not have to pack additional bags. Easy to open up and the Velcro has a nice hold of the divider when you stand it up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute Makeup Bag
reviews.reviewText: I received this bag in black with gold zippers. The color combination of black and gold really makes the bag stand out. The bag has separate compartments for brushes, makeup, powders, sponges, tweezers, etc. The top portion of the zippered bag, has a zippered compartment when you open it. and 8 small compartments to hold your brushes. The thick plastic material inside of the bag, makes it easy to wipe it clean when needed.The second zipper is the larger portion of the makeup bag with 2 netting compartments to store sponges or whatever you prefer, I use mine for makeup wipes. The large bottom portion holds a lot more and can also be separated by a divider that can be used as a separator held by velcro on each side of the bag. The divider has 2 netting pockets on one side and the other side of the divider has more separate spaces to place items that need to be held in place.It's a beautiful bag that serves its purpose, I would certainly recommend this bag and it's a great gift idea.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Size Makeup Bag
reviews.reviewText: This is a great makeup bag! I love the size and the way it's laid out. It's on the larger size which is perfect for my everyday needs, keeping things organized and in one place. I would not consider it a bag for travel as in my opinion, it would take up too much space for my preferences as I use a backpack and roll-on suitcase, and I hate checking my luggage. If you travel and check then this would fit in a standard suitcase with no issue. It's well organized and perfect on my counter but can be slid under the cabinet out of the way when needed.
